    <string name="welcome_tile_title">Welcome to KlippShell! 👋</string>
    <string name="welcome_tile_msg">Great to have you here! To help you get the most out of your printer monitoring, here is a quick overview of KlippShell\'s core features and the specific traits of some TV devices. KlippShell was designed to run smoothly on smartphones, tablets, or user-friendly on Android TV.\n\n1️⃣ FIRST STEPS\nAdd your first 3D printer below. Currently, almost all models on the market are integrated. If you want to use another printer based on Klipper, you can select \"Custom Model\".\nNote: Depending on the printer model and network configuration, you may need to manually adjust your ports and camera access to guarantee proper monitoring. However, the automatic network scan should cover most configurations automatically.\n⚠️ If you don\'t get a live image from the printer, please visit https://github.com/DnG-Crafts/K2-Camera and install the FIX. Unfortunately, this requires root rights on the printer!\n💡 Tip: A long press in the main menu on one of your saved printers opens the options to change the default view between live stream monitoring and Klipper OS, or to delete this printer.\n\n2️⃣ SMART LIVE CONTROL\nIn video stream mode, you control everything using three lower main buttons:\n• Left button: Opens the menu for On-Screen Display (OSD), video zoom, PiP, enclosure lighting, screensaver, and aspect ratio.\n• Middle button: Toggles seamlessly between Klipper OS (dashboard) and the pure camera live stream.\n• Right button: Safely returns you to the main menu at any time.\n\n3️⃣ DIRECT START MODE\nIf you have already successfully configured a printer, you can choose the direct start mode in the settings. This allows you to start directly in the live stream view when launching the app.\n\n4️⃣ COMPANION MODE\nWith KlippShell you can use your device as a TV dashboard (Master) or as a smartphone remote control (Slave). Activate the companion mode in the settings to control your TV comfortably from your smartphone.\n\n5️⃣ PICTURE-IN-PICTURE (PiP)\nAlthough KlippShell fully supports PiP, some TV manufacturers refuse to offer this feature natively. No worries: in the settings you will find an advanced feature with precise instructions on how to easily unlock PiP on your TV device using an ADB command!\n\n6️⃣ TV \"NOW LIVE\" FEATURE\nIf you want to use the \"Now Live\" TV feature, due to manufacturer restrictions, it may not be displayed natively on your TV dashboard. In this case, we recommend using an alternative TV launcher like the \"Projectivity Launcher\" to fully enjoy this feature.</string>
    <string name="welcome_tile_btn">Understood &amp; Hide</string>

